%N A395937 Decimal expansion of the expected distance between two points independently and uniformly selected at random one on each of two opposite faces of a unit cube.
%H A395937 Arak M. Mathai, Peter Moschopoulos, and Giorgio Pederzoli, <a href="https://rivista-statistica.unibo.it/article/view/1104">Distance between random points in a cube</a>, Statistica, Vol. 59, No. 1 (1999), pp. 61-81; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268489321">ResearchGate link</a>.
%H A395937 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CubeLinePickingFaceandFace.html">Cube Line Picking--Face and Face</a>.
%F A395937 Equals (3*sqrt(2) - 4*sqrt(3) + 4 - 10*log(2) + 20*log(1+sqrt(3)))/15 + arcsinh(1) - 2*Pi/9.
